@startuml
' @id(USE-RUN-CYCLE)
' @id(USE-BROWSE-TREE)
' @id(USE-GROUP-BY-CYCLE)
' @id(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW)
' @id(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
' @id(USE-ELEMENT-DESC)
' @id(USE-WHOLE-MAP)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
'
' Objective-side use cases for end-to-end MDD cycle tracking. These extend
' the existing viewer use case (USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS, defined in the
' diagram-viewer objective use-case file) with cycle-aware browsing,
' a before/after diff view, per-element descriptions, and a new
' single-description orchestration entry point.
'
' @desc marker contract: a one-line, human-readable sentence describing
' what a diagram element IS. Authored per significant @id by /mdd-map and
' /mdd-generate, validated by /mdd-validate, surfaced by the viewer in the
' right-hand MODEL CONTEXT card. Syntax: ' @desc(<ID>, "text")
'
' @desc(USE-RUN-CYCLE, "One-shot orchestration: run the whole MDD loop from a single feature/bug description, pausing only to ask clarifying questions.")
' @desc(USE-BROWSE-TREE, "Left rail is a VSCode-style collapsible directory tree of model files instead of a flat alphabetical list.")
' @desc(USE-GROUP-BY-CYCLE, "Alternative rail organization that groups diagrams under the cycle that last touched them.")
' @desc(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW, "Diff mode is bound to the model file selected in the left rail; the cycle is chosen only among the cycles that actually changed that file (default the latest such cycle), never a global picker.")
' @desc(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM, "Within Diff mode, an inner Diagram/List toggle: Diagram renders the file's superposed .diff diagram (additions green, removals red) on the canvas; List is the added/removed/unchanged text buckets for that same file.")
' @desc(USE-ELEMENT-DESC, "Selecting a diagram element shows its @desc text in the MODEL CONTEXT card, distinctly styled.")
' @desc(USE-WHOLE-MAP, "Each closed cycle accumulates its diff into a persisted per-concept .mdd/map/ baseline: added @ids are copied in with @cycle provenance, removed @ids drop out so add-then-remove nets to neither. The whole-map tree is snapshotted per cycle under .mdd/cycles/<N>/whole/, giving a whole-system picture as of each cycle. It is an inspection artifact outside the parity gate.")
title MDD cycle tracking — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Developer" as Dev

rectangle "mdd toolchain + viewer" {
  usecase "Run a full MDD cycle\nfrom one description" as RunCycle
  usecase "Browse models in a\ndirectory tree (VSCode-style)" as Tree
  usecase "Group diagrams by cycle" as Group
  usecase "View the selected file's\nbefore/after diff for a cycle" as Diff
  usecase "Toggle diff between a\nrendered diagram and the list" as DiffDiagram
  usecase "Read a diagram element's\ndescription" as Desc
  usecase "Accumulate a whole-map\nbaseline across cycles" as WholeMap
}

Dev --> RunCycle
Dev --> Tree
Dev --> Diff
Dev --> Desc
Dev --> WholeMap

Tree ..> Group : <<extend>>
Diff ..> Tree : <<include>>
Diff ..> DiffDiagram : <<extend>>
Tree ..> Desc : <<extend>>
RunCycle ..> WholeMap : <<extend>>

note right of RunCycle
  Entry-point selection:
  - description given  -> start at /mdd-generate
  - no description     -> behave exactly as
    /mdd-map with no comments does today
  Then: validate -> implement -> map ->
  validate -> review, looping on mismatch
  until parity closes. The skill PAUSES and
  asks the user whenever a modeling or
  implementation decision is genuinely
  ambiguous. It owns the cycle boundary:
  opens + snapshots before, closes +
  snapshots after + writes the diff pumls.
end note

note bottom of Diff
  Diff mode is keyed on the rail-selected
  file. The user is NOT asked to pick a
  cycle globally: the cycle row lists only
  the cycles that actually changed THIS file
  (its CycleDiff has added/removed elements —
  a written .diff; present-unchanged does NOT
  count), newest first,
  defaulting to the latest. One such cycle
  -> shown as a caption (no control); none
  -> "this diagram didn't change in any
  cycle" placeholder. Realized by
  SEQ-RENDER-CYCLE-DIFF.
end note

note bottom of DiffDiagram
  Inner toggle, default Diagram:
  - Diagram: the file's superposed
    <diagram>.diff.svg painted on the
    existing canvas (pan/zoom reused),
    additions green, removals red.
  - List: today's added/removed/unchanged
    text buckets, scoped to that one file.
  The diagram SVG is pre-rasterized by the
  pipeline (SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG); the viewer
  has no PlantUML engine and only consumes
  the rendered SVG.
end note

note bottom of Desc
  Per-element @desc text only; shown on
  element selection in the MODEL CONTEXT
  card. Realized by SEQ-ELEMENT-DESC.
end note

note bottom of WholeMap
  Produced by /mdd-cycle's Close step (extends
  RunCycle), never re-derived from code and not
  a /mdd-map mode. After the cycle's
  <diagram>.diff.puml is written, each touched
  concept's CycleDiff is applied to a persisted
  .mdd/map/<kind>/<name>.puml: added @ids copied
  from after/ tagged ' @cycle(<ID>,<N>),
  removed @ids (and their elements) deleted,
  unchanged @ids keep their earlier provenance.
  Net cancellation is automatic — a later
  remove physically deletes what an earlier
  cycle added (no ghost). .mdd/map/manifest.yml
  records last_cycle + files; the tree is
  snapshotted to .mdd/cycles/<N>/whole/.
  /mdd-render rasterizes .mdd/map/**.puml to
  .mdd/rendered/map/**.svg. Outside the parity
  gate: /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle loop never read .mdd/map/.
  Realized by SEQ-WHOLE-MAP-ACCUMULATE.
end note
@enduml
